(9, 'Bryan Stevenson talking about Justice', 'The Institutions for Development Department invites you to a presentation by Bryan Stevenson, Executive Director of the Equal Justice Initiative and Professor of NYU School of Law', '1430748016.jpg', 'Monday June 1st, 2015', '10.30am', 'Andres Bello Room', 'Called America\'s Nelson Mandela.\r\nOne of Time\'s 100 Most Influential People.\r\n\r\nHis Equal Justice Initiative is dedicated to help eliminate excessive and unfair sentencing, exonerating innocent death row prisoners, and confronting abuse of the incarcerated and the mentally ill and aiding children prosecuted as adults. \r\n\r\n\"Bryan Stevenson is Shaping the Moral Universeâ€, Desmond Tutu', 'Don\'t miss the chance to meet Bryan Stevenson. His TED talk holds the record for the longest standing ovation given to any TED speaker. Please be on time if you want to receive his book \"Just Mercy: A Story of Justice and Redemption\"', '2015-05-04 07:00:21', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(12, 'Datos destacados de IFD!', 'QuerÃ­amos contarles que dos conjuntos de datos de IFD/ICS ya estÃ¡n disponibles en el Portal de Datos Abiertos del BID. ', '', 'Donde puedes verlos?', 'Click en http://data.iadb.org/', '', '', 'Estos han sido los primeros dos conjuntos de datos destacados en el banner de NÃºmeros para el Desarrollo, la pÃ¡gina inicial del Portal de Datos Abiertos del BID. ', '2015-07-06 09:25:57', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(13, 'The role of Technocrats in Latin America: the cases of Colombia and Peru in the economy and health sectors', 'With the support of the\r\nInstitutional Capacity Strengthening Fund (ICSF), and the\r\nSpecial Program for Institutional Development (SPID) \r\n', '1436900510.png', 'July 28th, 2015', '12.30 pm', 'Andres Bello 3', 'Beginning in the eighties, but especially since the nineties in the context of market oriented reforms, more and more Latin American countries witnessed the appointment of technocrats to key state positions. During the past two decades technocrats have been praised by some as islands of efficiency, capable of carrying on key reforms in complicated scenarios. However, others have criticized them for removing wide areas of policy making from the democratic arena. Technocrats have become prominent and controversial actors in Latin American politics. \r\n\r\nWhy have these experts achieved considerable autonomy and influence?  Where does expertsâ€™ power over policy making come from if they lack an independent base of authority, such as popular election, or the tenure enjoyed by professional bureaucrats? And why do technocratic reform teams enjoy and maintain greater autonomy in some state areas than in others? \r\n\r\nIn this BBL, through an in-depth analysis of technocratic experiences in economics and health policy in Colombia from 1958 to 2011 and in Peru from 1980 to 2011, Eduardo Dargent provides answers for these and other questions about the role of technocrats in Latin America.  \r\n\r\nThe audience will have the opportunity to engage in a Q&A session, where issues of potential interest to countries in Latin America can be explored.\r\n\r\nProf. Dargent will be joined by Veronica Zavala, General Manager of the Office of Strategic Planning and Development Effectiveness and Carlos Santiso, Chief Division of the Institutional Capacity of the State Division who will comment on the research findings.\r\n\r\nPlease RSVP at ICSF/SECTEC@iadb.org or SPID-SECTEC@iadb.org. \r\n\r\nContact: Alejandra Carrasco alejandraca@iadb.org\r\n', 'a light lunch will be served', '2015-07-14 12:01:51', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(14, 'BBL: ICT as a driver of Public Sector Modernization ', 'Lessons from SAP', '1436980756.jpg', 'Thursday, July 23rd', '12:30 a 14:00 hrs.', 'SE-0745', 'Come and join us to learn about some of the most advanced experiences in the use of ICT for: fiscal management, human resource management, security and e-government services. \n\nSAP business experts will present us with some of the most successful cases they have developed in these areas during our BBL. \n\nSpeakers: \nMr. Paul Oâ€™Sullivan, Solutions Manager, SAP Labs\nMs. Teresa De La Guardia, IVE Public Sector SAP North Region- Latin America', 'This invitation is personal. Please confirm your attendance by accepting the Outlook Calendar event or by sending an email to Catalina Garcia de Alba, acgarcia@IADB.ORG.  ', '2015-07-15 10:19:18', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(15, 'BBL: The role of Technocrats in Latin America', 'The cases of Colombia and Peru in the Economy and Health Sectors \nWith the support of the Institutional Capacity Strengthening Fund (ICSF), and the Special Program for Institutional Development (SPID) \n', '1437079958.jpg', 'Tuesday, July 28th, 2015', '12:30 - 2:30 pm', 'Andres Bello 3', 'Beginning in the eighties, but especially since the nineties in the context of market oriented reforms, more and more Latin American countries witnessed the appointment of technocrats to key state positions. During the past two decades technocrats have been praised by some as islands of efficiency, capable of carrying on key reforms in complicated scenarios. However, others have criticized them for removing wide areas of policy making from the democratic arena. Technocrats have become prominent and controversial actors in Latin American politics. \n\nWhy have these experts achieved considerable autonomy and influence?  Where does expertsâ€™ power over policy making come from if they lack an independent base of authority, such as popular election, or the tenure enjoyed by professional bureaucrats? And why do technocratic reform teams enjoy and maintain greater autonomy in some state areas than in others? \n\nIn this BBL, through an in-depth analysis of technocratic experiences in economics and health policy in Colombia from 1958 to 2011 and in Peru from 1980 to 2011, Eduardo Dargent provides answers for these and other questions about the role of technocrats in Latin America.  \n\nThe audience will have the opportunity to engage in a Q&A session, where issues of potential interest to countries in Latin America can be explored.\n\nProf. Dargent will be joined by Veronica Zavala, General Manager of the Office of Strategic Planning and Development Effectiveness and Carlos Santiso, Chief Division of the Institutional Capacity of the State Division who will comment on the research findings.', 'A light lunch will be served. \nPlease RSVP at ICSF/SECTEC@iadb.org or SPID-SECTEC@iadb.org. \nFor further information contact Alejandra Carrasco alejandraca@iadb.org. ', '2015-07-16 13:52:41', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(16, 'Una Mirada al Futuro', 'La Gerencia del Departamento de Instituciones para el Desarrollo (IFD/IFD) los invita a una interesante presentaciÃ³n sobre el futuro', '1437429666.png', 'Lunes 10 de agosto', '3.00 pm', 'B-502', 'El futuro estÃ¡ entre nosotros. El crecimiento exponencial de la capacidad tecnolÃ³gica estÃ¡ cambiando rÃ¡pidamente los sistemas econÃ³micos, las relaciones sociales y la cotidianidad en nuestros paÃ­ses. Â¿CÃ³mo darle sentido a estos procesos de cambio? Â¿Hasta dÃ³nde puede llegar esta tendencia? Â¿CÃ³mo debe prepararse LAC y el BID para un futuro que se reconfigura diariamente? Carlos Felipe Reyes explorarÃ¡ escenarios posibles y formas de adaptaciÃ³n al futuro.\r\n\r\nCarlos Felipe es economista y abogado de la Universidad de los Andes (Colombia) y candidato a maestrÃ­as en polÃ­ticas pÃºblicas y planeaciÃ³n urbana de la Universidad de Harvard. TrabajÃ³ por cuatro aÃ±os en el gobierno de Colombia, como asesor del Ministro de Salud y ProtecciÃ³n Social y del Departamento Nacional de PlaneaciÃ³n.\r\n', '', '2015-07-20 15:01:11', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
