(18, 'El Departamento de Instituciones para el Desarrollo (IFD), con el apoyo de la DivisiÃ³n de Fortalecimiento de la Capacidad Institucional (ICS) y del Fondo de Transparencia, invitan ', 'Fortalecimiento del marco anti-corrupciÃ³n en Chile:  Recomendaciones del Consejo Asesor Presidencial Contra los Conflictos de InterÃ©s, el TrÃ¡fico de Influencias, y la CorrupciÃ³n', '1440455423.png', '28 de Septiembre, 2015 ', '2.30 pm ', 'EXD Lounge', 'A pesar de los avances en la lucha contra la corrupciÃ³n logrados a lo largo de las Ãºltimas dÃ©cadas, Chile, al igual que otros paÃ­ses de la regiÃ³n de AmÃ©rica Latina y el Caribe, enfrenta nuevos desafÃ­os; ante los que ha renovado sus esfuerzos para reformar su marco normativo en pro de la Ã©tica, integridad y transparencia, tanto en el Ã¡mbito pÃºblico como privado, y en la relaciÃ³n entre Ã©stos.\r\n\r\nEl pasado 11 de marzo de 2015, la Presidenta Michelle Bachelet creÃ³ el Consejo Asesor Presidencial Contra los Conflictos de InterÃ©s, el TrÃ¡fico de Influencias, y la CorrupciÃ³n, presidido por el Profesor Eduardo Engel, con el objetivo de proponer ese nuevo marco normativo. En este evento, el Prof. Engel presentarÃ¡ los resultados del trabajo del Consejo y las propuestas de reforma presentadas, en abril de este aÃ±o, a la Presidente Bachelet. \r\n\r\nEl Prof. Engel es Ingeniero Civil de la Universidad de Chile y PhD en EstadÃ­sticas de la Universidad de Standford y de EconomÃ­a del MIT. El Sr. Kevin Casas, ex-Secretario de Asuntos PolÃ­ticos de la OEA y ex-Vicepresidente de la RepÃºblica de Costa Rica;  y Cynthia Arnson, Directora del Programa de AmÃ©rica Latina del Wilson Center, proveerÃ¡n comentarios y reflexiones para situar los esfuerzos de Chile en materia de lucha contra la corrupciÃ³n en el marco de experiencias y esfuerzos similares en otros paÃ­ses de la regiÃ³n. \r\n', '', '2015-08-24 15:30:27', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(19, 'A Conversation on Big Data with Michael Flowers and Diego Molano', 'IFD and EXR invite you to join us for a discussion on               \r\nHow Big Data can be used to improve the lives and serve the needs of the LAC region?', '1441133049.jpg', 'Wednesday September 9th', '10.30am', 'B-502', 'The growth and availability of data is moving at exponential rates. 90% of the data in the world has been generated in the last 2 years and every day we create enough data to fill 10 million Blu-ray discs.  What can we do with this wealth of information? Join us for a discussion on how Big Data can be used to improve the lives and serve the needs of the LAC region.\r\n\r\nMichael Flowers is a former Chief Analytics Officer of New York City and Diego Molano is a former Minister of Information Technologies and Communications in Colombia.\r\n\r\n', '', '2015-09-01 11:44:11', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(20, '\"The Watchful Eye and the Cracking Whip: A Study on Corruption Monitoring\"', 'The Institutions for Development Department invites you to a presentation by Paul F. Lagunes, PhD, Assistant Professor of International and Public Affairs, Columbia University', '1447260960.jpg', 'Thursday September 24th', '12:30 pm ', 'NE-719', 'Professor Lagunesâ€™ research, built on participant observation and randomized experimental strategies, aims to understand how corruption works on the ground and how it can be reined in. He received his Ph.D. in Political Science from Yale University in 2012. \n\nProfessor Lagunes will present the above-referenced paper, which analyzes the impact of independent oversight on the behavior of bureaucrats in QuerÃ©taro, Mexico. With implications for law enforcement, the studyâ€™s results reveal that monitoring spurs greater diligence and stringency among officials, but only when they sense the risk of a top-down sanction. Additionally, Professor Lagunes will discuss ongoing research in Peru studying the relationship between government and NGO oversight of municipal officials and the quality of public investment.', 'with the support of the Transparency Trust Fund\n\nA light lunch will be served\n\nIf you wish to participate via VC please send an email to selvar@iadb.org', '2015-11-11 09:56:06', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
