(22, 'BBL: Transformando Vidas a travÃ©s de Presupuestos Abiertos', 'Las divisiones de GestiÃ³n Fiscal y Municipal (FMM) y Capacidad Institucional del Estado (ICS), le invitan a un BBL sobre los resultados mÃ¡s recientes de la Encuesta de Presupuesto Abierto de la organizaciÃ³n International Budget Partnership (IBP). La encuesta mide el estado de la transparencia presupuestaria, la participaciÃ³n y vigilancia en paÃ­ses alrededor del mundo.', '1444081218.png', 'Jueves 8 de octubre 2015 ', '12:30 a 14:00 ', 'SE-0745', 'Esta presentaciÃ³n tiene como objetivo exponer los resultados de la encuesta 2015 y detallar las sugerencias que paÃ­ses deben implementar para mejorar su gestiÃ³n de las finanzas pÃºblicas.\r\n\r\nEn este BBL Michael Castro, Oficial de Programas de la Iniciativa de Presupuesto Abierto del IBP presentarÃ¡ los resultados. Michael ofrece asistencia tÃ©cnica a organizaciones asociadas, gobiernos en AmÃ©rica Latina y el Caribe, Ãfrica Occidental y Asia Central para la implementaciÃ³n de dicha encuesta. Ha diseÃ±ado y ofrece cursos de formaciÃ³n sobre transparencia presupuestaria y  elaboraciÃ³n inclusiva de presupuestos a una variedad de organizaciones de la sociedad civil. TambiÃ©n ha proporcionado una amplia asistencia tÃ©cnica a los Gobiernos de RepÃºblica Dominicana, Honduras, Departamento del Reino Unido para el Desarrollo Internacional (DFID), entre otros.\r\n\r\nEl pÃºblico tendrÃ¡ la oportunidad de participar en una sesiÃ³n preguntas y respuestas. La presentaciÃ³n serÃ¡ en espaÃ±ol.\r\n\r\nPÃ¡gina del IBP - http://internationalbudget.org/ \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Se ofrecerÃ¡ un almuerzo ligero. ', '2015-10-05 14:40:25', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(23, 'IX Annual Meeting of the Electronic Government Network of Latin America and the Caribbean- Red GEALC', 'Thank you for joining representatives of 21 countries from our region in this important event.', '1446828350.jpg', '', '', '', 'Dear Mr. Sung Jo Kang, \r\n\r\nOn behalf of the Inter-American Development Bankâ€™s (IDB) Institutional Capacity of the State Division (ICS) we would like to reiterate our appreciation for your participation and that of the Korean Delegation in the IX Annual Meeting of the Electronic Government Network of Latin America and the Caribbean- Red GEALC, held on October 26th-27th in Mexico City. \r\n\r\nExperiences, results and examples shared by the participating countries reaffirm the importance of Digital Government policies as a platform to build new forms of governance. Knowledge and understanding of the success stories and best practices in this field as the ones presented during the Panel: Digital Korea, a model for global leadership on e-government provide a fundamental input  as countries in the region work on these policies to enable productive and constructive collaboration schemes between government and other stakeholders in society, \r\n\r\nWe would like to reaffirm the Bankâ€™s commitment to continue supporting these knowledge exchange efforts and the common needs that arose during the event.\r\n \r\nFinally, we are enclosing the commemorative photograph of the event and Mr. Alvaro Ramirez Alujasâ€™ blog post (Spanish): â€œGobierno Abierto en AmÃ©rica Latina y el Caribe: Los tiempos estÃ¡n cambiandoâ€ (http://blogs.iadb.org/gobernarte/2014/05/01/gobierno-abierto-en-america-latina-y-el-caribe-los-tiempos-estan-cambiando/ ), published in our new blog â€œGobernarteâ€. If you would like to contribute a post, please contact Selva Rodriguez (selvar@iadb.org). \r\n\r\nIn the coming days, the Dialogue Coordinator, Nicolas Dassen (nicolasd@iadb.org) will be sending the link to the web page through which we will be sharing all the documents and Power Points presented throughout the event. \r\n\r\nWe look forward to counting with your distinguished participation in our next efforts to advance the Open Government agenda in the region.\r\n\r\n\r\nBest Regards, \r\n', '', '2015-11-06 10:00:27', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(24, 'PRESENTATION Â¨Crime and Criminal Statistics: Latest Development and ChallengesÂ¨', 'Marcelo Aebi, Professor of Criminology and Deputy Director of the  School for Criminal Sciences at the University of Lausanne, Switzerland', '', '', 'Tuesday, November 17 1.15pm', '', 'Marcelo Aebi. Criminology professor and deputy director of the School of Criminal Science at the University of Lausanne, Switzerland. He has a Ph.D and M.A. in criminology from the University of Lausanne and a MA in Law from University of Buenos Aires. He has been a visiting professor at the Rutgers School of Criminal Justice (UE) and the Max Planck Institute for Foreign and International Criminal Law (Germany). He was assistant director and professor of criminology of the Andalusian Institute of Criminology at the University of Seville and associate professor at the Autonomous University of Barcelona (Spain). His main research interests include comparative criminology, corrections, methodology, juvenile delinquency, crime and victimization surveys and self- reported crime. He is also an expert consultant to the Council of Europe and the European Commission and the Executive Secretary of the European Society of Criminology.', '', '2015-11-13 15:17:46', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
