(28, 'Innovation, Entrepreneurship, and Industrial Organization, a research agenda', 'The Competitiveness and Innovation Division (CTI) is pleased to extend you an invitation to participate in a workshop where we will discuss the most recent trends in innovation and entrepreneurship economics. ', '1456438536.jpg', 'March 4, 2016', '9:00am', 'B-502', 'Speakers: \n- Nicholas Bloom, Stanford University \n- Roberto Ãlvarez, Universidad de Chile \n- Juan Miguel Gallego, Universidad del Rosario, Colombia \n- AndrÃ©s Rius, Universidad de la RepÃºblica, Uruguay ', '', '2016-02-25 15:15:40', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(29, 'BBL: Smart Nation Harnessing technology to improve citizens\' lives, create more opportunities, and build stronger communities', 'Key lessons from ICS Study Mission to Singapore', '', 'Monday, February 29, 2016', '12:30 - 02:00 pm', 'B-302', 'A Smart Nation means people and businesses are empowered through increased access to data, more participatory through the contribution of innovative ideas and solutions, and a more anticipatory government that utilizes technology to better serve citizensâ€™ needs.\r\nSingapore has taken a leadership position in terms of modernization of the State with intensive incorporation of ICT as a lever for delivering efficient, effective and transparent services; ranking 1/143 countries in the World Economic Forum Networked Readiness Index 2015 and 3/193 in UNDESA E-Government Development Index 2014. \r\nRecognizing the relevance of the identification, consolidation, systematization and dissemination of knowledge about the promotion of innovation within the public administration at the international level, and more specifically about the policies and initiatives that have been successful in strengthening governmental capacity to provide better solutions to citizenâ€™s demands through innovation; the Institutional Capacity of the State (ICS) Division of the Institutions for Development (IFD) Department with the support of the Knowledge and Learning Sector Cutting Edge Knowledge Fund, organized a study mission to Singapore to learn more about this countryâ€™s journey towards building the World\'s first Smart Nation. \r\nCome and join us to learn more about the lessons learned from our specialists that participated in this mission. \r\nSpeakers:\r\n\r\nï¶	Miguel PorrÃºa (IFD/ICS)\r\nï¶	Mauricio GarcÃ­a Mejia (IFD/ICS)\r\nï¶	Robert Pantzer (IFD/ICS)\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Coffee will be provided. \r\nFor further information on the event, please contact Catalina Garcia de Alba, acgarcia@IADB.ORG. ', '2016-02-23 12:49:19', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(30, 'GestiÃ³n de Propiedad Intelectual y GeneraciÃ³n de Valor:', 'El Caso de CafÃ© de Colombia y Juan Valdez', '1456862747.jpg', 'Martes 8 de marzo de 2016', '12:30pm', 'NE-1069', 'En este BBL contaremos con la participaciÃ³n de Luis Samper, quien liderÃ³ la estrategia de propiedad intelectual de la FederaciÃ³n de Cafeteros en Colombia, organizaciÃ³n que representa a mÃ¡s de 500 mil productores, generando nuevos negocios y regalÃ­as de marca por valor superior a 20 millones de dÃ³lares. \nEn esta presentaciÃ³n se mostraran las experiencias de monetizaciÃ³n y generaciÃ³n de activos intangibles y transables, a la vez que se plantearan los retos que enfrentaron los diferentes actores para que los instrumentos de PI fueran  utilizados en las estrategias de cooperaciÃ³n y generaciÃ³n de valor  de diferentes empresas y organizaciones.\n\n', 'SE SERVIRÃ UN ALMUERZO LIGERO', '2016-03-01 13:05:49', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
(31, 'Providing Energy to the BOP in Haiti: Can The Private Sector Do It?', 'A Social Entrepreneurâ€™s Experience ', '1458067712.jpg', 'March 18, 2016', '1:00 pm â€“ 2:00 pm', 'NE-1069', 'Social Entrepreneur Darragh Dolan walks you through his journey of providing social services in Haiti using innovation and technology, amidst a challenging business, infrastructure and economic environment. \r\n\r\nInstitutions for Development through the Competitiveness Innovation and Technology Division (IFD/CTI) invites you to join us in a highly fascinating discussion on innovating and doing business in Haiti. \r\n\r\nAs highlighted in the Private Sector Development Report (PSAR) on Haiti, we explore the potential of providing basic services to bottom of the pyramid (BOP) and the private sector challenges faced by social entrepreneur Darragh Dolan who, through direct support from the Compete Caribbean program, pioneered in creating Revolt â€“ a pay-as-you-go solar powered, energy service to marginalized communities. Experiences from another of his projects â€“ Surtab, which manufactures low-cost tablets in Haiti â€“ will also illustrate the main arguments.', 'A light lunch will be served', '2016-03-15 11:48:36', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
