(59, 'BBL: The Digital Society- A brief history of Estonia e-government\'s journey ', 'The most advanced digital society in the world is a former Soviet Republic on the edge of the Baltic Sea. -WIRED Magazine', '1490631421.png', 'Wednesday, March 29', '13:00 - 15:00 hrs.', 'NE-719', 'A few hours ago, Ben Hammersley from WIRED published: \"...And by handing over â‚¬50 [since this story was published, this price has increased to â‚¬100] and a Â­photograph, allowing my fingerprints to be taken and waiting a few weeks while my Â­credentials were verified, I have been issued with an identity card, a cryptographic key and a PIN code to access its national systems. I am now an official e-resident of the Republic of Estonia, as is the Japanese prime minister, and you will want to be one, too. And what\'s more, by doing so, you\'ll be part of a system that could not only reinvent public services for the internet age, but Â­fundamentally redefine what it means to be a country.\"\n\nSource: http://www.wired.co.uk/article/estonia-e-resident \n\nWant to learn more about Estonia\'s digital journey? Come and join us for a BBL with Siim Sikkut. \n\nMr. Sim Sikkut is a Digital Policy Adviser at Government Office of Estonia. He specializes in ICT policy and trends, information society development, e-governance, strategic policy-making, management and innovation in public sector, emerging markets (specifically China and India), futures thinking and foresight and global mega-trends. He is also member of board in the e-Residency Programme and is one of the founders and stewards of Estonian governmentâ€™s e-Residency Programme. Additionally, he is member of supervisory board in the E-Governance Academy whereby he gave strategic advice to e-governance think-tank, consulting and training agency. Mr. Sikkut has a diverse experience and is an active participant in his field. Some of his experience includes being a member of the Information Society Council, economic expert in the Estonian Development Fund, advisor in the Ministry of Finance of the Republic of Estonia, Deputy Head of State Budget Department and head of Development Unit in the State Budget Department and Chief Specialist in State Budget Department in the Ministry of Finance of the Republic of Estonia.', 'A light lunch will be provided. \nPlease confirm your attendance by accepting the Outlook Calendar event. ', '2017-03-27 09:39:11', 0, '', '', '', '', ''),
