(38, 36, 'Connected Citizens', 'Cada dÃ­a se producen 2.5 trillones de bytes de datos, de los cuales un 80% es capturado y administrado por empresas privadas. A su vez, AmÃ©rica Latina es la regiÃ³n con mayores niveles de uso y tasa de crecimiento de las redes sociales en el mundo. En este escenario, el potencial del uso de datos masivos (Big Data) para optimizar la polÃ­ticas pÃºblicas y la comunicaciÃ³n entre gobiernos y ciudadanos trae al centro de la escena interrogantes sobre la disponibilidad de la informaciÃ³n y el origen de un nuevo tipo de alianzas pÃºblico-privadas para el intercambio de datos.\n\nMiguel Guevara presentarÃ¡ el caso de Waze (Google) y su programa Connected Citizens, a travÃ©s del cual la empresa se asocia con gobiernos para el intercambio bi-direccional de datos. Nueve ciudades latinoamericanas participan de este programa, accediendo a insumos para la gestiÃ³n del transporte urbano en base a datos georreferenciados de los usuarios de Waze y sus reportes de accidentes. \n\nEn este BBL conocerÃ¡s en quÃ© consiste el intercambio de datos y cuÃ¡les son las ventajas para las partes involucradas.', '', '', '2016-03-24 11:59:19', '#003163'),
(39, 38, 'Join us for a presentation on CAFâ€™s flagship publication by Pablo Sanguinetti, Chief Economist, and his team. ', 'In the discussion about what are the best public policies for development it is often assumed that the State has the capacity to successfully design and implement these interventions. But this is not always so. There are numerous cases of policies that fail to achieve the expected results because of the lack of capacity on the part of the agencies responsible for putting policies into practice. The present edition of the Report on Economics and Development puts at the center of the debate the analysis of the capacities to design, implement and learn from public policies. Among these capacities is notably the bureaucracy as a crosscutting component throughout the policy production cycle; public procurement systems as a crucial tool to effectively implement programs; citizen participation to strengthen accountability; and finally, monitoring and evaluation schemes to transform experiences into knowledge and learning to increase the effectiveness of the entire process.\n\n', '', '', '2016-04-05 08:17:21', ''),
